  <p>
    Jakarta has the strongest healthcare infrastructure in Indonesia, though quality across the city remains uneven. Indonesia operates a mixed public–private system, with just under 3,000 hospitals nationwide. While the number of facilities has grown quickly, public hospitals remain under pressure. For most expats, healthcare planning centres on private hospitals, backed by international health insurance to manage cost, access, and risk.
  </p>

